A trainee pilot narrowly escaped death after a light aircraft he was flying crashed near Malindi airport on Thursday. The plane crashed on the roof of a house at Furunzi, a few metres from the runway. The pilot was alone. The pilot was rushed to Malindi hospital in critical condition before being transferred to Mombasa for specialised treatment . Hundreds of curious onlookers flocked to the scene. The aircraft was extensively damaged. Police have taken up the matter with a view to establishing what caused the crash. Click here for more political news      